  "description": "You control any freestanding water within a 100\u2011foot cube that you choose. While the spell lasts you can select one of four effects: Flood \u2013 raise the water level up to 20 feet or create a 20\u2011foot\u2011tall wave; Part Water \u2013 split the water to form a trench that later refills; Redirect Flow \u2013 force flowing water to move in any direction you choose; Whirlpool \u2013 create a vortex up to 25 feet tall that pulls creatures toward it, dealing 2d8 bludgeoning damage on a failed Strength saving throw. As an action on your turn you may repeat the same effect or switch to a different one.",
